Topics Reviewed
Data Security States

Data in Use

Refers to data actively being processed by applications or systems (e.g., databases or running applications).

Cloud-Native Architecture

Cloud-native applications are designed for scalability, resilience, and distributed infrastructure.

Systems may use failover and load balancing across multiple geographic regions to maintain high availability.

Network Access Control

NAC (Network Access Control)

Enforces security policies on devices attempting to access the network.

Often used for wired and wireless access control.

Web Application Vulnerabilities

Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)

Occurs when malicious scripts are injected into trusted web applications.

Can allow attackers to execute scripts in a user’s browser session.

Endpoint Web Filtering

Agent-based filtering

Installs a software agent on endpoints.

Allows filtering policies to apply regardless of device location (on or off the network).

Security Monitoring

SIEM

Aggregates and analyzes logs from multiple systems.

Used to detect anomalies and security incidents.

Network Protection

Firewalls

Monitor and control incoming and outgoing network traffic.

Apply predefined security rules to allow or block communications.

Activity Accounting

Tracks user activities such as:

Logins

Resource usage

File access

Supports auditing, billing, and security monitoring.

Mobile Device Management

MDM

Allows organizations to monitor, secure, and manage mobile devices remotely.

Enforces policies for employee devices accessing company data.

Data Governance Roles

Data Custodian

Responsible for implementing and maintaining data protection policies.

Manages technical controls such as storage, access, and maintenance according to organizational policies.

